<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="55.[264,1323,399,1905]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">ETYMOLOGY. The specific name alludes both to the difficulty in resolving many fine characters, because of the tenacity of the dorsal secretions, and to the extreme crypsis of the feeding stages on leaf surfaces.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[264,1323,284,590]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
COMMENTS. Few of the puparia of the 
<typeStatus box="[831,881,284,310]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
sample have benefitted from direct examination of the cuticular surface, such was the difficulty in removal of the tough dorsal carapace of secretion (see comments on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2005" box="[757,934,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Tegmaleurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[757,934,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Tegmaleurodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 47–48). It is clear, however, that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2005" box="[316,432,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptus">
<emphasis box="[316,432,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">T. cryptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not fall within one of the species­groups of 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1169,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1169,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Trialeurodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, L. M." box="[264,440,444,470]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref34886" refString="Russell, L. M. (1948) The North American species of whiteflies of the genus Trialeurodes. Miscellaneous publications. United States Department of Agriculture, 635, 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="1948">Russell (1948)</bibRefCitation>
. Despite the similarities of the dorsal secretions, the much smaller number and different form of the submarginal papillae, combined with the pronounced tracheal combs, places this species distantly from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quaintance &amp; Baker" authorityYear="1915" baseAuthorityName="Quaintance" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[794,947,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="floridensis">
<emphasis box="[794,947,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">T. floridensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
­group. No other known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[296,445,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,445,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Trialeurodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely to be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="2005" box="[790,905,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Trialeurodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptus">
<emphasis box="[790,905,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">T. cryptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
